title: Rock Sample
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a textured surface. The rock appears to have a mix of gray and yellowish hues, suggesting a mineral composition that may include various elements.

title: Mineral Sample
description: A rock specimen featuring a predominantly black exterior with striking orange veins running through it, suggesting a unique mineral composition.

title: Yellow Crystal
description: A close-up view of a yellow crystal with a rough, textured surface. The crystal has a shiny appearance and is composed of multiple facets, reflecting light in various directions.

title: Rock
description: A rough, irregularly shaped rock with a light beige color and a textured surface.

title: Underground Mine Tunnel
description: A dimly lit underground tunnel with rough, rocky walls. The tunnel has a dirt floor and metal tracks running along the ground, suggesting it is used for mining. Lights are mounted on the walls, illuminating the path ahead.

title: White Rock
description: A small, irregularly shaped white rock with a slightly rough texture and some visible crystalline structure.

title: Obsidian Rock
description: A piece of obsidian, a naturally occurring volcanic glass, characterized by its shiny black surface and smooth texture. The rock has a jagged shape with some reflective qualities, indicating its glassy nature.

title: Open-Pit Mine
description: A panoramic view of an open-pit mine, showcasing steep, terraced walls with vibrant colors ranging from orange to yellow and gray. The mine is filled with water, reflecting the surrounding landscape and sky, creating a striking contrast with the earthy tones of the mine walls.
